            I have a slight problem with the role of the Committee of the Regions. Fundamentally, whatever its internal structure&#x2014;whether it takes the Swedish model, according to which it cannot legislate but can raise taxes, the German Lander model or our model&#x2014;delivery is up to the individual member states, not the European Union. The flow of information should go to national Parliaments, who may then decide how to deliver it sub-regionally.
